ed motion support\n8. Properly organized and commented code\n\nThe CSS is now ready to be used with the HTML fragments created by the structurer worker. All validation errors have been resolved, and the file is properly formatted.\n\n### interactor\nI've created the JavaScript file (app.js) with the requested functionality:\n\n1. CTA Button Feedback:\n   - Adds a loading state when clicked\n   - Changes button text to \"Processing...\"\n   - Disables the button during processing\n   - Restores original state after 1.5 seconds\n\n2. Form Validation:\n   - Validates email format using the specified regex\n   - Prevents form submission if email is invalid\n   - Shows error messages for invalid emails\n   - Provides real-time validation feedback\n   - Simulates successful submission for valid emails\n\n3. Accessibility Features:\n   - Uses proper ARIA attributes (aria-invalid, aria-disabled, role=\"alert\")\n   - Maintains focus management\n   - Provides status updates with aria-live\n\nThe JavaScript is written in modern ES6+ syntax, uses event delegation where appropriate, and follows web accessibility best practices. It's lightweight and won't block the main thread.\n\n### integrator\nThe final landing page has been successfully assembled and validated. The index.html file includes all the necessary HTML structure with proper semantic elements, links to the styles.css file for styling, and includes the app.js script for interactive functionality. The HTML has been validated and contains no errors.\n\n### tester\n<tool_call>\n<function=render\n\n## Files Created\n- content.txt: TITLE: Unlock Your Potential: The Ultimate Guide to Personal Growth\n- structure.fragments.html: <!-- FRAGMENT: header -->\n- styles.css: :root {\n- app.js: document.addEventListener('DOMContentLoaded', () => {\n- index.html: <!DOCTYPE html>\n- mobile-view.png: PNG image\n- tablet-view.png: PNG image\n\n## Dynamic Tools Used\n[\n  \"validate_js_syntax\",\n  \"simulate_user_interaction\"\n]\n\n#